kb:cosmos-nano rdf:type     ktype:Feature ;
               rdfs:label   "NVIDIA Cosmos3-Nano" ;
               kpred:has-status   "speculative" ;
               kpred:description  "16B-parameter omnimodal world foundation model for Physical AI. Generates and reasons over video, images, audio, and robot actions. OpenMDW 1.1 license (commercial use). Requires NVIDIA GPU (Ampere/Hopper/Blackwell), BF16 precision, Linux. Potential uses: generate preview animations from entity descriptions, 3D scene understanding for graph visualization, multimodal graph ingest (video/image/audio sources). Shares NVIDIA GPU sidecar infrastructure with NeMo Speech." ;
               kpred:depends-on   kb:nemo-speech ;
               kpred:open-question "Massive resource requirements (16B params, BF16) — viable only for users with high-end NVIDIA GPUs. Evaluate smaller distilled variants when available." ;
               kpred:open-question "Integration path: same Python sidecar as NeMo Speech? Separate container? Which Cosmos capabilities map to graph workflows (video→triples, entity→animation)?" .

