# -- n8n Cloud Sync (F20) -------------------------------------------------------

kb:n8n-cloud-sync rdf:type ktype:Feature ;
               rdfs:label   "n8n Automation" ;
               kpred:data-egress  "third-party-service" ;
               kpred:gated-by     kb:content-safety ;
               kpred:has-status   "functional" ;
               kpred:feature-id   "F20" ;
               kpred:principle    "n8n is NOT a backend for all things Reckons.AI. It is an OPTIONAL, PER-USER automation layer: a user connects their OWN self-hosted n8n to enable personalized automation/integration flowing into AND out of their Reckons.AI. The app stays local-first with no general backend; n8n owns web side-effects, never core state. (Mirrored in CLAUDE.md → Integration Boundaries for coding agents.)" ;
               kpred:description  "Route web integrations through a self-hosted n8n instance (open-source automation, no SaaS). The clean division of labour: the app stays static/offline-first and owns the VISUAL building; n8n owns the web side-effects (email, sheets, tickets, monitoring). settings.n8nBaseUrl (Settings → Integrations) points at the instance." ;
               kpred:has-workflow  kb:n8n-sync-hub ;
               kpred:has-workflow  kb:n8n-source-monitor ;
               kpred:has-use-case  kb:n8n-contact-form ;
               kpred:remaining    "PARTIALLY WIRED (2026-07-10). DONE: Settings → Integrations n8nBaseUrl field, and the first end-to-end app use case — the contact form (kb:n8n-contact-form). STILL UNWIRED: graph upload/download via the Sync Hub webhooks, and currents register/pull via the Currents Monitor (F29.2) — the integration code exists (src/lib/integrations/n8n/currents-sync.ts) but nothing calls it from the app yet. Status scaffolded -> functional now that one real path works. Remaining: wire graph sync + currents, and verify against the live VPS." .

