               kpred:description  "Consider VR/AR/XR as the premier UI/UX for sets: in an immersive 3D graph, batch-select by looking/pointing or a lasso volume, GRAB nodes and gather them with hand/controller gestures, and drop them into a set; manipulate, split, and re-arrange sets in space (ties to F59 spatial layout + F60 arrange). Builds on the existing VR/AR shells (F7, VRShell/ARShell + WebXR) and the game-engine option (F59.1) for richer spatial rendering. XR turns the clunky Ctrl+click multi-select into a direct, embodied action." ;
               kpred:depends-on   kb:vr-ar-shells ;
